BFN 

  [Text] Budapest, May 18 (XINHUA) -- Zhang Wannian, chief 
of the General Staff of the Chinese People's Liberation Army, 
met Hungarian Defense [Minister] Lajos Fur here today and they 
discussed ways of expanding cooperation between the armed forces 
of the two countries. 
  General Zhang is leaving today for home after concluding his 
six- day visit to Hungary. During the visit, Zhang held talks 
with Hungarian leaders and top military officials on increased 
cooperation between the armed forces of the two countries and 
that in other fields. 
  Zhang also visited some grassroots units of the Hungarian 
Army. 
  Prior to Hungary, Zhang had visited Romania and Poland. 

